Drive Mapping Using Group Policy
Requirement

Active Directory Domain Services

Shared folder created on server

Proper share and NTFS permissions

Client machine joined to domain

Example Used
Shared Folder Path: \\SERVERNAME\SharedData
Drive Letter: Z:

PART 1: Verify Shared Folder

Ensure shared folder is accessible

Test access:

\\SERVERNAME\SharedData

PART 2: Create Group Policy Object (GPO)
Step 1: Open Group Policy Management

Login to Domain Controller

Open Server Manager

Click Tools

Select Group Policy Management

Step 2: Create New GPO

Right-click Domain or OU

Click Create a GPO in this domain, and Link it here

GPO Name:

Drive Mapping Policy


Click OK

PART 3: Configure Drive Mapping
Step 1: Edit GPO

Right-click Drive Mapping Policy

Click Edit

Step 2: Navigate Policy Path
User Configuration
→ Preferences
→ Windows Settings
→ Drive Maps

Step 3: Create New Drive Map

Right-click Drive Maps

Click New → Mapped Drive

Step 4: Configure Drive Map

Action: Create

Location:

\\SERVERNAME\SharedData


Drive Letter:

Z:


Label as:

Shared Drive


Click OK

PART 4: Link GPO to Correct OU

Ensure GPO is linked to OU where users are located

If not, drag or link the GPO to correct OU

PART 5: Apply Group Policy on Client
Step 1: Update Policy

Login to client machine

Open Command Prompt

Run:

gpupdate /force

Step 2: Logoff / Restart

Logoff and login again

Verification

Open This PC

Confirm mapped drive:

Z: Shared Drive

Common Issues & Fix

Drive not visible:

Check DNS settings

Check permissions

Check GPO linked to correct OU

Access denied:

Check Share and NTFS permissions

Conclusion

Drive mapping has been successfully configured using Group Policy in Active Directory.
